<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FFDD22456EDA868B" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FFDD22456EDA868B" blockId="1.[112,753,1661,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD22456CBE87AB" bold="true" box="[113,235,1661,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FF5A22456E6587AB" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[246,560,1661,1685]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FF5A22456E6587AB" box="[246,560,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Pseudomicrocentria uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257CAFFA35663FDED22456E9B87AB" box="[577,718,1661,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is characterised by a long and narrow radix abruptly bent in the middle. The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FDA522866E2D87EB" authorityName="Locket" authorityYear="1982" box="[521,632,1725,1749]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FDA522866E4287EB" box="[521,535,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FD8B22856E2D87EB" box="[551,632,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from the border between 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FE4222E56E0F87CB" box="[494,602,1757,1781]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FFDD22C56C80862B" box="[113,213,1789,1813]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, but it can easily be distinguished by the shape of the palpal tibia (
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FE8823256D26860B" box="[292,371,1821,1845]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[114,1454,170,1411]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[92,1470,170,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of male palp structure of Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, paratype (7–11), and P. simplex Locket, 1982 (12–13), after Locket (1982). 7, right palp, retrolateral view; 8, 13, right palp, prolateral view; 9, palpal patella, tibia, and paracymbium, prolateral view; 10, 12, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 11, distal part of embolic division. Scale = 0.1 mm. Figs. 11–13, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FE3223256DBB860B" box="[414,494,1821,1845]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[114,1454,170,1411]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[92,1470,170,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of male palp structure of Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, paratype (7–11), and P. simplex Locket, 1982 (12–13), after Locket (1982). 7, right palp, retrolateral view; 8, 13, right palp, prolateral view; 9, palpal patella, tibia, and paracymbium, prolateral view; 10, 12, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 11, distal part of embolic division. Scale = 0.1 mm. Figs. 11–13, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), as well as by the bent radix (
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FF1623056CAF866B" box="[186,250,1853,1877]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[114,1454,170,1411]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[92,1470,170,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of male palp structure of Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, paratype (7–11), and P. simplex Locket, 1982 (12–13), after Locket (1982). 7, right palp, retrolateral view; 8, 13, right palp, prolateral view; 9, palpal patella, tibia, and paracymbium, prolateral view; 10, 12, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 11, distal part of embolic division. Scale = 0.1 mm. Figs. 11–13, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FE8923056D20866B" box="[293,373,1853,1877]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[114,1454,170,1411]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[92,1470,170,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of male palp structure of Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, paratype (7–11), and P. simplex Locket, 1982 (12–13), after Locket (1982). 7, right palp, retrolateral view; 8, 13, right palp, prolateral view; 9, palpal patella, tibia, and paracymbium, prolateral view; 10, 12, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 11, distal part of embolic division. Scale = 0.1 mm. Figs. 11–13, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Both Oriental species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FD2C23066EBA866B" authorityName="Locket" authorityYear="1982" box="[640,751,1853,1877]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FD2C23066EDA866B" box="[640,655,1854,1877]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FD3223056EBA866B" box="[670,751,1853,1877]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FF3123666D54864B" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[157,257,1885,1909]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FF3123666CF8864B" box="[157,173,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FF1523666D54864B" box="[185,257,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257CAFFA35663FEA223656DDA864B" box="[270,399,1885,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, besides having differences in the genitalic structure, differ from their Afrotropical congener, 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FFDD23A66D47868B" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1970" box="[113,274,1949,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutissima">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD23A66CD4868B" box="[113,129,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FF3D23A66D47868B" box="[145,274,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">minutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the normal, not enlarged eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FFDD23E56EA5892B" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FFDD23E56EA5892B" blockId="1.[113,752,2013,2069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD23E56CA686CB" bold="true" box="[113,243,2013,2037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a Latin adjective, meaning “bent”, referring to the shape of the radix in the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FC8124856FBA82EB" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FC81248569C38008" blockId="1.[811,1451,189,310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FC8124856FED81EB" bold="true" box="[813,952,189,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Description.</emphasis>
I describe the 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FBF1248668EC81E8" box="[1117,1209,190,214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">paratype</typeStatus>
here to avoid causing damage to the 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FC6B24E5687D81CB" box="[967,1064,221,245]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
. Somemeasurements of the 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FAE124E569FF81CB" box="[1357,1450,221,245]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
are given in brackets. Carapace and abdomen shapes, body and leg colouration of 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FB8B252568D1800B" box="[1063,1156,285,309]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
are same as in 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FA9E252669C48008" box="[1330,1425,286,310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">paratype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FC812565686182A8" blockId="1.[811,1454,349,918]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
Male 
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FCCB25666F918048" box="[871,964,350,374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">paratype</typeStatus>
. Total length: 1.30 (
<quantity id="4C9D9B46FFA35663FB2325656882804B" box="[1167,1239,349,373]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2512" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" unit="in" value="1.28">1.28 in</quantity>
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FB7025656969804B" box="[1244,1340,349,373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
). Carapace unmodified (as in 
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FC5B2545686280AB" box="[1015,1079,381,405]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1232,1254]" captionTargetBox="[137,1472,189,1218]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[117,1490,186,1234]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, male paratype (1), Ummeliata jambi, new species, male holotype (2–4) and female paratype (5–6). 1–2, male body, dorsal view; 3–4, male prosoma, lateral and frontal views, respectively; 5, female body, dorsoventral view; 6, female abdomen, ventral view. Scale = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576944/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), 0.63 long, 0.48 wide (0.63 and 
<quantity id="4C9D9B46FFA35663FC8125A56F2E808B" box="[813,891,413,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1684" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" unit="in" value="0.46">0.46 in</quantity>
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FC2925A56FB3808B" box="[901,998,413,437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
, respectively), pale greyish brown. Eyes normal, not enlarged, sulci absent. Chelicerae 0.30 long, mastidion absent. Legs pale brown. Leg I 1.53 long (0.43 + 0.20 + 0.35 + 0.30 + 0.25), IV 1.56 long (0.43 + 0.20 + 0.35 + 0.35 + 0.23). Chaetotaxy: 2.2.2.1. Length of spines 1–1.5 diameters of corresponding leg segment. TmI 0.48 (
<quantity id="4C9D9B46FFA35663FC9826656FD6834B" box="[820,899,605,629]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" unit="in" value="0.5">0.50 in</quantity>
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FC2126656FBA834B" box="[909,1007,605,629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
). Metatarsus IV without trichobothrium. Palp (
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FCDC26456FB983AB" box="[880,1004,637,661]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[114,1454,170,1411]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[92,1470,170,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of male palp structure of Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, paratype (7–11), and P. simplex Locket, 1982 (12–13), after Locket (1982). 7, right palp, retrolateral view; 8, 13, right palp, prolateral view; 9, palpal patella, tibia, and paracymbium, prolateral view; 10, 12, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 11, distal part of embolic division. Scale = 0.1 mm. Figs. 11–13, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Figs. 7–11</figureCitation>
): Tibia slightly elongated, with a small rounded process antero-retrolaterally. Paracymbium very small, L-shaped. Tegulum with a sharp outgrowth distally. Distal suprategular apophysis short, more or less transparent, with a small tooth at base. Median membrane reduced. Convector absent. Radix long, narrow, abruptly bent in the middle. Embolus very short, slightly curved. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="135E2A26FFA35663FC9A27656F2D824B" box="[822,888,861,885]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1232,1254]" captionTargetBox="[137,1472,189,1218]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[117,1490,186,1234]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Pseudomicrocentria uncata, new species, male paratype (1), Ummeliata jambi, new species, male holotype (2–4) and female paratype (5–6). 1–2, male body, dorsal view; 3–4, male prosoma, lateral and frontal views, respectively; 5, female body, dorsoventral view; 6, female abdomen, ventral view. Scale = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4576944/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) 0.65 long, 0.45 wide (0.63 and 
<quantity id="4C9D9B46FFA35663FB5C2765696B824B" box="[1264,1342,861,885]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2192" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" unit="in" value="0.48">0.48 in</quantity>
<typeStatus id="54DE8801FFA35663FAE4276569FC824B" box="[1352,1449,861,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
, respectively), dark grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FC8127856FBA82EB" blockId="1.[813,1007,957,981]" box="[813,1007,957,981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FC8327C569CD852B" box="[815,1432,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FC8327C569CD852B" blockId="1.[815,1432,1021,1045]" box="[815,1432,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FC8327C56F94852B" bold="true" box="[815,961,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Distribution.</emphasis>
So far known only from Sabah, 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FA8527C569C1852B" box="[1321,1428,1021,1045]" name="Indonesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
